enggalakkan kerjasama dan perkongsian pengetahuan boleh membantu anda berkembang lebih cepat sebagai peniaga.\n\nMemilih firma penilaian Forex yang tepat adalah penting untuk kejayaan perdagangan anda. Untuk membuat keputusan yang bijak, adalah penting untuk menilai beberapa faktor utama: proses penilaian firma, model pembahagian keuntungan, dasar pengurusan risiko, instrumen perdagangan yang tersedia, perkhidmatan sokongan, struktur yuran, reputasi, dan peluang penglibatan komuniti. Firma penilaian yang dipilih dengan baik akan menyediakan modal, sokongan, dan sumber yang diperlukan untuk berkembang dalam pasaran Forex yang pantas. Luangkan masa untuk menyelidik pilihan anda dengan teliti dan pilih firma yang paling sesuai dengan gaya perdagangan dan objektif anda, memberikan anda peluang terbaik untuk berjaya.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}], "direction": "ltr"}}', '5 min baca', 'f', 't', NULL, NULL, NULL, 90, 'ms', 21),
('Understanding Common Mistakes to Avoid in Forex Funded Account Challenges', '1. The Importance of a Well-Defined Trading Plan Exciting but Challenging: Embarking on a Forex-funded account challenge offers the unique opportunity to manage substantial capital. Critical Error: A common mistake is neglecting to have a well-defined trading plan. Purpose of a Trading Plan: Acts as a roadmap guiding decisions on risk management, trade entries/exits, and [&hellip;]', 'understanding-common-mistakes-to-avoid-in-forex-funded-account-challenges', '{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "1. The Importance of a Well-Defined Trading Plan\n\n\n\n\nExciting but Challenging: Embarking on a Forex-funded account challenge offers the unique opportunity to manage substantial capital.\n\n\nCritical Error: A common mistake is neglecting to have a well-defined trading plan.\n\n\nPurpose of a Trading Plan: Acts as a roadmap guiding decisions on risk management, trade entries/exits, and market conditions.\n\n\nConsequences of No Plan: Trading without a plan can lead to significant losses.\n\n\nAction Step: Spend time crafting a detailed trading plan and adhere strictly to it.\n\n\nContinuous Improvement: Regularly review and adjust the plan based on performance and market changes.\n\n\n\n\n2. Avoiding Overtrading and Managing Risk\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\nTrading Pitfall: Pressure to meet targets can lead to excessive trading, which often results in unnecessary losses and emotional burnout.\n\n\nDiscipline Required: Set daily or weekly trading limits and focus on high-probability trades aligned with your strategy.\n\n\nRisk Management: Another critical mistake is poor risk management.\n\n\nRisk Management Rules:\n\n\nNever risk more than 1-2% of your account on a single trade.\n\n\nEnsure every trade has a stop-loss